{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857153967,"sessionID":"ses_286abd5e2ffeEPOa84aCziiVzz","part":{"id":"prt_d7955b783001ZVh5nBcIKr1D41","messageID":"msg_d7954c435001kF39pcmeblFUSL","sessionID":"ses_286abd5e2ffeEPOa84aCziiVzz","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-bcc8f6fb1a0246ef9a0fd2cca17f6158","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/proposal.md","content":"# AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement Redis and Valkey storage backends for AgentCube session management, providing high-performance, persistent storage with dual-provider support. This implementation provides:\n\n1. **Dual Backend Support**: Redis (`go-redis/v9`) and Valkey (`valkey-go`) implementations selectable via `STORE_TYPE`\n2. **Session Metadata Persistence**: Store `SandboxInfo` JSON documents keyed by session ID\n3. **GC Indexes**: Sorted sets for expiry-based and last-activity-based garbage collection queries\n4. **Singleton Pattern**: Thread-safe initialization via `sync.Once` with klog fatal on failure\n5. **Atomic Operations**: Pipeline/multi-command batching for store/delete operations\n6. **Graceful Error Handling**: `ErrNotFound` sentinel for missing session keys\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/store/store.go` | `Store` interface with 9 methods: Ping, GetSandboxBySessionID, StoreSandbox, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes, UpdateSessionLastActivity, Close |\n| `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Provider constants (`redis`, `valkey`), `Storage()` singleton accessor, `initStore()` initialization logic |\n| `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | `redisStore` struct implementing `Store` interface using `go-redis/v9` |\n| `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | `valkeyStore` struct implementing `Store` interface using `valkey-go` |\n| `pkg/store/doc.go` | Package documentation |\n| `pkg/store/store_test.go` | Unit tests for interface compliance, error handling, edge cases |\n\n### Key Components\n\n```\npkg/store/\n├── Store interface (store.go)\n│   ├── Ping(ctx) error\n│   ├── GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n│   ├── StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error — SETNX + ZADD expiry + ZADD activity (pipeline)\n│   ├── UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error — SET XX only\n│   ├── DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error — DEL + ZREM (pipeline)\n│   ├── ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)\n│   ├── ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)\n│   ├── UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error\n│   └── Close() error\n│\n├── Errors (store.go)\n│   └── ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n│\n├── Singleton (singleton.go)\n│   ├── redisStoreType = \"redis\"\n│   ├── valkeyStoreType = \"valkey\"\n│   ├── initStoreOnce = sync.Once{}\n│   ├── provider Store\n│   ├── Storage() Store → initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)\n│   └── initStore() error → reads STORE_TYPE, builds provider\n│\n├── Redis Implementation (store_redis.go)\n│   ├── redisStore struct\n│   │   ├── cli *redisv9.Client\n│   │   ├── sessionPrefix = \"session:\"\n│   │   ├── expiryIndexKey = \"session:expiry\"\n│   │   └── lastActivityIndexKey = \"session:last_activity\"\n│   ├── Environment: REDIS_ADDR, REDIS_PASSWORD, REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\n│   └── Commands: PING, GET, SETNX, SET XX, DEL, ZADD, ZREM, ZRANGEBYSCORE\n│\n├── Valkey Implementation (store_valkey.go)\n│   ├── valkeyStore struct\n│   │   ├── cli valkey.Client\n│   │   ├── Same key constants as Redis\n│   ├── Environment: VALKEY_ADDR (comma-separated), VALKEY_PASSWORD, VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED, VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE, VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\n│   └── API: B().Ping(), B().Get(), DoMulti (SETNX/ZADD/ZADD), SET XX, Zrangebyscore, Mget\n│\n└── Test Coverage (store_test.go)\n    ├── Ping connectivity\n    ├── CRUD operations\n    ├── ZSET index operations\n    ├── ErrNotFound scenarios\n    ├── Nil/zero validation\n    ├── Missing key tolerance in List*\n    ├── Singleton initialization\n```\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Redis Cluster deployment (single-node focus; Valkey supports comma-separated addresses)\n- Distributed lock implementation\n- Cache preheating strategy\n- Data migration tools\n- Redis Sentinel support\n- Session data encryption\n- Rate limiting on storage operations\n- Watch/subscribe for real-time updates\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Impact |\n|------------|--------|\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client library — Redis implementation |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client library — Valkey implementation |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Logging singleton init failure |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | `SandboxInfo` struct definition |\n| `context` | Operation timeout/cancellation support |\n| `encoding/json` | SandboxInfo serialization |\n| `time` | Timestamp handling for expiry/activity |\n| `sync` | Singleton initialization guard |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| Session Manager (`pkg/router/session_manager.go`) | Query/create/update sessions via `Storage()` |\n| Router (`pkg/router/server.go`) | Session lookup for request routing |\n| Workload Manager (`pkg/workloadmanager/`) | Create sandbox → `StoreSandbox`; delete → `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` |\n| Garbage Collector (`pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`) | `ListExpiredSandboxes` / `ListInactiveSandboxes` for cleanup |\n\n### Breaking Change Considerations\n\n- **Store Interface Signature**: Adding/removing methods requires all implementations to update\n- **Key Pattern Changes**: Changing `session:` prefix or ZSET keys breaks existing data\n- **Environment Variable Names**: Rename requires deployment updates\n- **ErrNotFound Message**: Changing `store: not found` message breaks error comparison\n- **SandboxInfo Fields**: Missing JSON tags or new fields affect stored documents\n- **Singleton Fatal Behavior**: `klog.Fatalf` on init failure crashes process; must handle env validation before production\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Single Redis Backend Only\n\n**Approach**: Implement only Redis, skip Valkey support.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Simpler codebase; single dependency; fewer tests |\n| Cons | Locks into Redis vendor; Valkey is open-source Redis alternative with better licensing; limits deployment flexibility |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Valkey is LF-supported Redis fork; dual support provides vendor flexibility without significant complexity overhead (same data model, similar APIs).\n\n### Alternative 2: In-Memory Storage\n\n**Approach**: Use `sync.Map` or map with mutex for in-memory storage.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | No external dependency; simpler deployment; fast local access |\n| Cons | No persistence (restart loses data); no distributed access; no GC indexes without custom implementation |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Production requires persistence for session continuity across restarts and distributed access for multi-instance deployment.\n\n### Alternative 3: Etcd Storage\n\n**Approach**: Use Etcd as storage backend.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Strong consistency; Kubernetes-native; built-in watch/lease |\n| Cons | Higher latency than Redis/Valkey; heavier resource footprint; overkill for session metadata |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Session storage prioritizes low-latency reads/writes over strong consistency. Redis/Valkey sorted sets provide efficient expiry/activity queries.\n\n### Alternative 4: Database Storage (PostgreSQL/MySQL)\n\n**Approach**: Use relational database with session table and indexed columns.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Strong consistency; familiar SQL queries; existing DB infrastructure |\n| Cons | Higher latency; heavier for simple key-value patterns; connection pool complexity |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Session data is simple key-value with time-based queries. Redis/Valkey sorted sets are optimal for `ZRANGEBYSCORE` expiry/inactivity lookups.\n\n### Alternative 5: Pipeline vs. Individual Commands\n\n**Approach**: Execute `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` as separate commands without pipeline.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Simpler code; easier error handling per command |\n| Cons | Multiple round trips; partial success leaves inconsistent state (key exists without ZSET entry) |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Pipeline/multi ensures atomic batch: all commands succeed or fail together, maintaining consistency between session key and ZSET indexes.\n\n## Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Redis/Valkey connection failure | Env validation on init; `Ping` for health check; singleton fatal catches early |\n| Missing password with required=true | Explicit check: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` to disable |\n| ZSET orphan members (key deleted, ZSET entry remains) | `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` skips missing keys without error |\n| Key collision across namespaces | Key pattern `session:{sessionID}` uses globally unique session ID |\n| Pipeline partial failure | Redis pipeline returns all errors; Valkey `DoMulti` fails on any error |\n| Clock skew for expiry scoring | Unix timestamp scoring is absolute; relies on server clock accuracy |\n| Singleton race condition | `sync.Once` guarantees single initialization |\n| Valkey MGET slot requirement | Comment notes keys should be in same slot; deployment must ensure consistent hashing |\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Key Pattern**: `session:{sessionID}` for JSON documents\n2. **Expiry ZSET**: `session:expiry` — member = sessionID, score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n3. **Activity ZSET**: `session:last_activity` — member = sessionID, score = `at.Unix()` or `time.Now().Unix()`\n4. **SETNX for Store**: Prevents duplicate session creation\n5. **SET XX for Update**: Enforces key must exist before update\n6. **ZRANGEBYSCORE**: `-inf` to `{before.Unix()}` for expiry/inactivity queries\n7. **ErrNotFound**: Redis `redis.Nil` → `ErrNotFound`; Valkey `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound`\n8. **STORE_TYPE**: Case-insensitive; defaults to `redis`; only `redis` or `valkey` accepted\n9. **Password Required**: Default true; set `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` or `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` to disable\n10. **Singleton Fatal**: `initStore` error → `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`; process exits\n\n## References\n\n- `session-store/design.md` — Detailed design specification\n- `session-store/spec.md` — Requirements and scenarios\n- `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` — `SandboxInfo` struct definition\n- `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client reference\n- `changes/AR-012/proposal.md` — Related interface definition (if exists)\n- [go-redis v9](https://github.com/redis/go-redis)\n- [valkey-go](https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go)"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/common/types/sandbox.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":60,"character":40},"end":{"line":60,"character":71}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#omitzero"},"source":"omitzero","message":"Omitempty has no effect on nested struct fields"}]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775857153938,"end":1775857153965}}}}
